The APC Civic Support Group and the Nigerian Engineering Youth for Good Governance have called on President Muhammadu Buhari to give 40 per cent of ministerial slots to youths. The groups, in conjunction with the Nigerian Labour Congress, Nigerian Youth Re-Orientation for True Democracy and the Not Too Young To Rule movement, also urged ‎ Senate President Ahmed Lawan and Speaker House of Representatives, Femi Gbajabiamila,‎ to support their call. They stated this at a news briefing in Kaduna, saying Buhari’s re-election should be a platform for youths to make their contribution in moving the country forward. Engineer Adamu Suleiman Yakubu who spoke on behalf of the groups equally harped on the need for President Buhari to appoint technocrats to head engineering related ministries. APC support group wants 40 percent appointment for youths in Buhari’s cabinet Lagos youth c’ttee inaugurates 114-member team for Buhari ‘Youth support critical to Buhari’s victory’ Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin